    Simran Singh Bansal
    4.0 out of 5 stars Great Sound Quality and Value for Money, But Replace the Ear Caps!
    Reviewed in India on 23 July 2023
    Colour: BlueSize: All SizesVerified Purchase
    I purchased the Oppo Enco Buds back in February 2023, and they have been my go-to earbuds ever since. Overall, I am quite satisfied with their performance and features.

    The sound quality of the Oppo Enco Buds is truly impressive. The audio is clear, with well-defined highs and punchy bass. The Dolby Atmos feature adds an extra dimension to the listening experience, making movies and music more immersive. I have to say, for the price point, these earbuds deliver exceptional audio performance.

    The battery life is decent, lasting me through extended listening sessions without any issues. Additionally, the connectivity has been reliable, and I haven't experienced any major dropouts or disconnections.

    The build quality of the earbuds is sturdy and feels durable. The case is compact and easily slips into my pocket, making it convenient to carry around. The touch controls work well and are responsive, which is a nice touch.

    However, one area where the Oppo Enco Buds fall short is the noise cancellation. While it is present, I found it to be just average. It does a decent job of reducing ambient noise, but it could have been better, especially in noisy environments.

    My biggest gripe with these earbuds is the quality of the included silicone ear caps. They are of subpar quality and not very comfortable for prolonged use. They don't fit securely, leading to concerns about the earbuds falling out during workouts or other activities. Fortunately, I found a suitable alternative in the Boult silicone caps, which fit perfectly and provide a more comfortable and secure fit.

    Despite the minor shortcomings, I must emphasize that the Oppo Enco Buds are undeniably value for money. If you're willing to invest in some better ear caps separately, you'll be rewarded with an exceptional audio experience.

    In conclusion, if you're in search of earbuds with great sound quality and impressive Dolby Atmos support without breaking the bank, the Oppo Enco Buds are an excellent choice. Just make sure to consider investing in better ear caps for a more comfortable and secure fit.
